reviewText: Jeff Jarrett VS Ahmed Johnson-A good opener with Ahmed looking impressive, including Johnson diving over the top rope and nailing Jarrett with a cross body block. The ending sucked with Jarrett coming off the top rope and hitting Johnson in the head with a guitar.Bodydonna's VS Smoking Gunns-A good match that also included anther over the top rope cross body block. The ending was awesome.Razor Ramon VS Goldust-Good story going in and the match had alot of stalling. It was a decent match up and the action picked up towards the end. 1-2-3 Kid nails Ramon with a spinning heel kick from the top rope and cost Ramon the title. Overall, enjoyable but not much of a match.The Royal Rumble: The worst Rumble ive seen yet, and ive seen everyone of them. It had alot of good wrestlers but a few wrestlers who never even competed in the WWF. Shawn Michaels wins it again but I could care less.Undertaker VS Bret Hart: A decent main event and Diesel ruins the Undertaker's chance of winning it.Overall, not much of a show. First two matches were good, the IC title match was more story telling and show then wrestling, the Rumble sucked, and the main event had a crappy ending. They did make up for it at WrestleMania though.
Title: WWF: Royal Rumble 1996 VHS

reviewText: 1996 was when the WWF began to get some real momentum going again after a few pretty bad years recovering from the losses of Hulk Hogan, Ultimate Warrior, and Ric Flair.While this PPV is certainly erratic, it also has a lot going for it.  (Matches rated on a scale of * to ****)Ahmed Johnson Vs. Double J/Smoking Gunns Vs. Body Donnas-  Two totally forgettable matches.  Like I said, they wern't completely on track yet.  *Razor Ramon Vs. Goldust- People tend to forget how much real heat Goldust had going into this match, and it was shocking at the time that he won the IC Title.  Both men are certainly in their prime at this point, and despite the anticlimactic ending, this match tells a good story.  ***Royal Rumble Match-  If you could sit through any Royal Rumble match from 1993 to 1995, you're stronger than I am.  This one at least has a lot of really great wrestlers in it: Shawn Michaels, Diesel, Yokozuna, Vader, Steve Austin, Triple H.  It's very entertaining.  ***On a side note, to me the highlight of the PPV by far was the return of Jake 'The Snake' Roberts.  The ovation he gets gives you goosebumps.  It's a shame that his comeback was so unsuccessful due to the sterilization of the character, as well as his own failings.Bret Hart Vs. The Undertaker-  It's too bad this match is not that good; Bret Hart was probably peaking and The Undertaker had not had such momentum going into a World Title match since his first in 1991.  Unfortunately, the style of these two men just don't click; they both need someone a little bit faster paced to have a great match.I liked that it was implied that Undertaker would have pinned Hart though, they at least gave him that as he would not capture the WWF title for another year.  **1/2The Royal Rumble PPV's would steadily improve for the next few years until about 2001, this fun event shows a step in the right direction.
Title: WWF: Royal Rumble 1996 VHS

reviewText: Another old WWF tape that I found in my collection in the 1996 Royal Rumble. During this time, Bret Hart was the WWF Champion who was taking on all comers but seemed to run into his stiffest challenge yet in The Undertaker, who was the number one contender. Also, Shawn Michaels was making his return to see if he was capable of doing what he did the year before & that was win the Royal Rumble one more time. On top of that, Goldust was playing mind games with Intercontinental Champion Razor Ramon who had continuing issues with the 1-2-3 Kid as well.Ahmed Johnson vs Jeff Jarrett. This was Jarrett's last WWF match till about late 1997 before going to WCW but this was more of a showcase for Ahmed as he over-powered Jarrett throughout this match before Jarrett got himself disqualified by hitting him with a guitar off the top rope.WWF Tag Team Champions The Smoking Gunns vs The Body Donnas. For those that don't know or remember, this version of the Body Donnas was Skip (who was ECW's Chris Candido) & Rad Radford. A great tag team match between these two teams with the Donnas actually using some great tag team tactics by cutting the ring in half at times before the Gunns did the same thing to counter their offense.Intercontinental Champion Razor Ramon vs Goldust. The storyline here was that for months, Goldust had been trying to get the attention of Razor to the point where he even wrote him a letter. The psychology of this match was worked out great as the early stages of the match had some comedic stalling with Goldust playing more "mind games" including a moment where he did a waist lock but decided to just rub Razor's chest. Once that got out of the way, this was a solid contest that went back & forth before the 1-2-3 Kid interfered to cost Razor the title & set up their Crybaby match a month later.Royal Rumble Match. Most fans consider this to be the worst Rumble ever but I heavily disagree as I really enjoyed this one. Moments include Triple H lasting the longest in the Rumble, the debut of the Ringmaster (Steve Austin), Razor Ramon getting his revenge on the Kid, the WWF debut of Vader who actually came in & dominated the Rumble for the most part before getting into a confrontation with Yokozuna that lead to the surprise moment of Shawn Michaels tossing both men over the top rope at the same time which lead to Vader snapping & going back in to eliminate everyone in the Rumble including a confrontation with WWF President Gorilla Monsoon, Jake Roberts returning & clearing the ring with his snake & even placing it on Jerry Lawler that scared him to the point where he was under the ring for most of the Rumble. Shawn Michaels would go on to win his second Rumble in the end.WWF Champion Bret Hart vs The Undertaker. Before the match started, there was a brawl in the entrance way between Undertaker & Diesel due Diesel being angry about being eliminated from the Rumble. Once that was done, this was the more unique performance that the Undertaker had at this time as both men worked well together & put on a great wrestling match with Taker working on Bret's back & even using moves he had not used before including a claw hold while Bret just targeted the leg with aggression that played a factor at times during the match. The ending was a bit of a jib with Diesel interfering to cost Taker the title but it didn't take away from what was a great match between these two that would be topped by their series in 1997.So in the end, this Rumble did a great job of continuing storylines (Razor/Kid) as well as starting up new ones (Diesel's official heel turn that lead to his feud with Undertaker, HBK's quest for the gold at WrestleMania, Vader/Yoko) while delivering a great action throughout making this one WWF event that I would go out of my way to see.
summary: The Road To WrestleMania XII Begins
Title: WWF: Royal Rumble 1996 VHS

reviewText: Now it is time for a retro wrestling review The 1996 Royal Rumble I have all the episodes from 1996 of RAW so I can fill in the backstory leading into each Pay Per View. On The January 8th episode of RAW Shawn Michaels announced that I am going into The Royal Rumble. On The December 18th episode of Raw Goldust cut a messed up promo he said "Razor Ramon your the man that ooze's machismo on January 21st lets ooze it together." On The January 1st episode of RAW he got gold roses. On The January 13th episode of WWF Superstars Mr Perfect gave Razor Ramon a gift from Goldust. On The January 15th episode of RAW Razor attacked Goldust they fought in the hallway all the way outside until Goldust got in his car & escaped. That is pretty much the backstory. The buyrate for this event was a 1.10 that is up from last years Rumble.The current WWF Champions are as followsWWF ChampionBret Hart November 19th 1995WWF Intecontintal ChampionRazor Ramon October 22nd 1995WWF Tag Team ChampionshipThe Smoking Gunns Billy & Bart September 25th 1995Date January 21, 1996Attendance 9,600[1]Venue Selland ArenaCity Fresno, CaliforniaFree For AllDok Hendrix interviewed the debuting Vader he cut an awesome promo.Todd Pettengill interviewed Jake "The Snake"Roberts who said he has dealt with a lot of deamons & now tonight 29 other men will deal with them.Duke "The Dumpster" Drose Def Hunter Hearst Helmsley by disqualification * & half of a star in a watchable match the winner got to enter number 30 in The Rumble the loser had to enter number 1. Hunter used some knucks but Gorilla Monsoon reversed the decison.They show a video package for The Intercontintal title match.Shawn Michaels comes out for an interview. Todd Pettengill asked Shawn what number he drew he said he's number 1 but if you're asking what number I drew for in The Rumble I'll come in when I want & I'll leave when I want & that's when I'm the last man in the ring. He said my destiny to The WWF Championship starts here. Dok Hendrix interviewed Hunter Hearst Helmsley who is mad that Gorilla Monsoon reversed the decison.We open up The Pay Per View with Sunny telling us viewer discretion is advised.The opening is amazingAhmed Johnson Def Jeff Jarrett by disqulification * & a quarter of a star2nd DQ of the night if count the match from The Free For All. Jarrett's guitar shot from the top rope was pretty funny.Todd Pettengill interviewed Diesel who said people have been woundering where my head is at. Let me tell you I'm a 9th grader my parents have left me home alone for the 1st time I don't know what I'm going to do. But I know that I am going to have the time of my life.WWF Tag Team ChampionshipChampions Smoking Gunns Def The Bodydonna's Skip & Zip with Sunny * & half of a star a watchable match but kind of boring at the same time. At least Sunny was cute.Then they show Billionare Ted's Wrasslin War Room I know that people say Vince was being hypocritical but these tell the truth about how WCW was eing ran in the mid to late 90's.WWF Intercontintal ChampionshipGoldust with Marlena Def Champion Razor Ramon * & half of a star this happend to be the debute of Marlena aka Terri Runnels. This was watchable once again but also kind of boring. 123 Kid interfered gave Razor Ramon a spinning thrust kick off the top rope.They show comments from The Superstars who entered The Royal Rumble.Royal Rumble MatchShawn Michaels won last eliminating Diesel **** & a half of a staralso involving Hunter Hearst Helmsley, Henry Godwin, Bob Backlund, Jerry Lawler, Bob Holly, Mabel Jake"The Snake" Roberts,  Dory Funk, Yokozuna, 123 Kid, Omari, Savio Vega, Big Van Vader, Doug Gillbert, Swat Team NO 1, Swat Team No 2 Owen Hart, Shawn Michaels, Hakushi, Tatanka, Also Mytoya, Kama, Steve Austin, Barry Horowitz, Fatu, Issac Yankem, Marty Janetty, The British Bulldog & Duke "The Dumpster" DroseShawn Michaels of course got a shot at The WWF Championship at Wrestlemania XII.Diesel was super p  i  s  s  e  d about losing Shawn Michaels decided that it would be a good idea to moon the crowd. Diesel headed back to the ring he gave Shawn a high 5. He also celebrated with the crowd.WWF ChampionshipUndertaker with Paul Bearer Def  Champion Bret Hart by disqualifiction *** before the match Diesel & The Undertaker got into it when Undertaker was coming down to the ring. This was a pretty good match watching it again. My only complaint is that it started off too slow like they were going to wrestle for an hour. This is also where that cool mask The Undertaker was wearing came off. Diesel interfered he got Bret Hart DQ'ed Diesel flipped off The Dead Man. Todd Pettengill interviewed Gorilla Monsoon he announced that Bret Hart will defend The WWF Championship against Diesel at In Your House 6. Dok Hendrix interviewed Shawn Michaels he said phase 1 of his destiny has been completed & that I will be the man in 96. Undertaker came in when Todd Pettengill was talking to Gorilla Monsoon. He said it will be a cold day in h  e  l  l when Diesel wears The WWF Championship again. Monsoon said that I don't want to see what happend here happen at the next Pay Per View. So he added a Steel Cage stipulation.Dok Hendrix interviewed Diesel he said that I'm the only reason that Bret Hart lives & breaths. You don't have to like me. But you sure have to love me cuase I'm the best thing going. He added in 1996 it's no longer The World Wresting Federation it's The Diesel Wrestling Federation. Todd Pettengill interviewed Jim Cornette Vader was tearing his locker room up.I'm being nice this Pay Per View was decent not including the match from The Free For All you had a poor Jeff Jarrett vs Ahmed Johnson match. The Tag Team title match was watchable but not very good. The intercontintal title match Goldust vs Razor Ramon that was watchable but still not very good. The Royal Rumble match was great & a pretty good WWF title match. Again if you want to see it go find a seller that sells old WWF PPV's. But my next wrestling review will be WWF In Your House 6 Rage In The Cage.
Title: WWF: Royal Rumble 1996 VHS

reviewText: The Ahmed Johnson-Jeff Jarrett match was a good/solid brawl with a "Smashing" ending to make it sweeter. The tag team title match between The Smoking Gunns(Billy & Bart) & The Bodydonnas(Skip & Zip) was a classic back-and-forth bout. The IC title between Goldust(Dustin Rhodes) & Razor Ramon(Scott Hall) was a fun & entertaining match with a ending that you will get a "kick" out of. The Royal Rumble match while not a bad bout,it had some dumb moments like Jerry Lawler running under the ring after seeing Jake Robert's snake and HBK winning the thing was kind of predictable & obvious. The World title match between Bret Hart & The Undertaker was a good solid bout which was ruined by Diesel's interference. I give this event a 8 out of 10.
Title: WWF: Royal Rumble 1996 VHS

reviewText: This was a split event with half good and half bad matches. The good matches though were good enough to save the pay-per-view. Here are the matches.1. Double J vs. Ahmed Johnson 8/10A decent opener, but it was way too short. It was funny to see Double J get beat up real bad by Ahmed Johnson. Ahmed Johnson also took a real hard fall from the top rope trying to do some high-flying move too. The ending sucks with Ahmed winning by DQ because Jeff Jarrett (Double J) hit Ahmed with the guitar.2. Skip and Zip (The Bodydonnas) vs. Billy Gunn and Bart Gunn (The Smoking Gunns) 7/10An okay match. I was not expecting much from this match anyway, but it had a few really good moves in it on the part of the Smoking Gunns. The Smoking Gunns retain their Tag Team Titles.3. Goldust vs. Razor Ramon 8/10This match really good. It was good to see both of these good wrestlers fight too. There were a few good moves but towards the end it started to get a little boring which made it seem like it was long (which is not good). The ending was kind of suprisng with Goldust becoming the new WWE Intercontinental Champion. It happened when the 1-2-3 Kid came from the crowd and went to the top rope and kicked Razor Ramon REAL HARD! That allowed Goldust to get the pin and the victory.4. The Royal Rumble 9/10This was a good Royal rumble. A lot of people say there were no- namers but I knew most of them except for like 5 people I did not know. Other than that it was fun. Stone Cold Steve Austin made his Royal Rumble debut here as well. Some of the highlights was when Henry Godwinn threw some nasty stuff at Jerry Lawler, Jake The Snake Roberts coming in and letting his snake out and all of the wrestlers clear the ring (under the ropes). When this happened Jake put the snake on Jerry Lawler, and then Jerry Lawler hid under the ring for like 30 minutes until Shawn Michaels eliminated him with a hard punch. Some more higlights was when Shawn Michaels eliminated Vader and Yokozuna simultaniously. Shawn Michaels wins this Royal Rumble (which made it two years in a row) by eliminated Diesel (superkicked him over the top rope!). Good Rumble.5. The Undertaker vs. Bret Hart 7/10This was a real bad main event. It had a couple of good moves but that did not save it. These two guys also faught a lot outside too. This match was way too long as well, it was like 30 minutes long! The ending sucks when The Undertaker wins by DQ because Diesel came. Bret retains his WWE Title.
Title: WWF: Royal Rumble 1996 VHS

Title: WWF: Royal Rumble 1996 VHS

reviewText: Royal Rumble 1996 began the birth of the era of the Heartbreak Kid so a speak. Michaels won his second Rumble match here. Undertaker and Bret Hart gave an unbelieveable match for the main event.1. Jeff Jarrett vs. Ahmed JohnsonThis could have been a good match but it was average and nothing more. Jarrett did his dirty tactic moves and Ahmed pulled off some impact slams. The match did had a good guitar smash at the end. 2.5/52. Tag Team TitlesSmoking Gunns vs. The Body Donnas with SunnyThis was the donnas ppv debut I believe and they had a very good match with Bart and Billy. Bart and Billy also had some miscues with each other cause of Sunny. A tag match worth a watch here. 3.5/53. IC TitleRazor Ramon vs. Goldust with MarlenaQuite an interesting and fun match to watch. Goldust was all about his little funny and unusual inring techniques which he is known for. Cheap tactics was used by Goldust to get the advantage over Razor. Goldust and Razor had a nice match up. 123 Kid would hit Razor with the heel kick from behind and cost Razor the match. 4/54. The Royal Rumble MatchThis Rumble match wasn't great but it was good but it also felt like something was missing for some reason but it still was a good rumble.Triple H had an awesome showing from entering number one and lasting nearly 50 minutes. Most of the throws over the top rope came at good spots. You would even forget about the fact that the King hides under the ring for about 30 minutes. HBK also had a good showing and he especially spiced things up once he entered the match. Steve Austin entered this rumble as the ringmaster and he too gave a nice performance. But the true highlight was when Vader and Yokozuna got in each other faces. The last elimination was great. Like I said, not a great rumble but this surely is one of the better ones. 4.25/55. WWE TitleUndertaker with Paul Bearer vs. Bret HartThis is one of those matches which Taker fought with that mask he wore due to the injury he suffered from Yokozuna. Before the match got underway, Taker and Diesel had a brawl which began their fued and led to their match at Mania 12, but Taker and Hart certainly delivered another classic. I felt this match was better than their Summerslam match but not better than their one night only match from the UK. Taker's leg takes a mouthful of punishment in this one. Hart just really torques and beats on the leg of Taker. Great action inside and outside of the ring. Couldn't ask for anything more and the dq from Diesel didn't hurt the match whatsoever. The deadman and the hitman delivers another classic match right here. 5/5Rumble '96 is worth getting. You won't regret on buying this, just don't spend a lot on it.
summary: The Main event delivered and a whole lot more
Title: WWF: Royal Rumble 1996 VHS

reviewText: When Hulk Hogan's "prime" in the WWF finally came and went in the early 1990s, the torch was passed to Bret "Hitman" Hart, who actually could put on a better show in his sleep than Hogan ever could dream of.  Unfortunately, following the abdication of Hogan, the WWF was not able to support its top superstar with any other top-tier talent, and this fact was never more apparent than at Royal Rumble 1996.From top to bottom, this was a terrible card.  The preliminary matches were incredibly lackluster (the character of "Goldust" only proves how low the WWF was stooping at this time), the Rumble was filled with fat guys, has-beens, and a few 100% jobbers, and event the main event (Hart-Undertaker) didn't live up to past billings.  Long gone are the days of exciting characters and thrilling matches, replaced instead by weirdos and stereotypes that don't elicit any sort of emotional connection with the fans/viewers.Unless you are a die-hard WWF junkie, please do not spend one cent of your finances on this three-hour snoozefest.
Title: WWF: Royal Rumble 1996 VHS
